VP can be expressed using variables and
common events, separate from those
directly input for SE and screen
effects.

By inputting the corresponding variables
in 925~928 and executing Common Events
391~394, you can play SEs that match
each situation.

If you want to repeat an SE, it will
repeat for the number of times entered
in variable 932 (the repeated SE will
play a random appropriate SE).

For flashes and screen effects, you can
express them by executing variable 933
and Common Event 397.

For details, please refer to the
relevant section of the "About
Modifications" item in recent ci-en
articles.

Besides this, you can also continuously
play sound effects using BGS, so feel
free to create events without being
limited to the above functions.

I've compiled a simple list of various
SEs that seem likely to be used for

save the created event information
externally, or else you won't be able to

the other for primary data saving to
